and more clothes and…

810
00:35:01,405 --> 00:35:05,450
I was never a materialistic man, Rose.

811
00:35:05,534 --> 00:35:08,620
I cared about science and thought

812
00:35:08,704 --> 00:35:11,206
and bettering mankind. Now look at me.

813
00:35:11,290 --> 00:35:13,041
I'm wearing two sweaters.

814
00:35:13,125 --> 00:35:16,503
Rose, tell me, when did I become a man

815
00:35:16,587 --> 00:35:19,506
who needs five bedrooms?

816
00:35:19,590 --> 00:35:23,425
When did I become a man
who… who needs a linen closet?

817
00:35:23,509 --> 00:35:25,678
When did I become a man who has a maid?

818
00:35:25,762 --> 00:35:27,721
When did I change?

819
00:35:27,805 --> 00:35:29,640
When did I become this selfish,

820
00:35:29,724 --> 00:35:31,976
materialistic man?

821
00:35:32,060 --> 00:35:35,020
Th… The kind of man I used to despise.

822
00:35:35,104 --> 00:35:37,564
-When you married me.
-I didn't say that!

823
00:35:37,648 --> 00:35:38,857
Hi, it's me!

824
00:35:38,941 --> 00:35:41,235
I just have to change
and get back to the airfield.

825
00:35:41,319 --> 00:35:42,569
Hey, what happened to my clothes?

826
00:35:42,653 --> 00:35:44,613
Have you worn all these dresses?

827
00:35:44,697 --> 00:35:46,156
-Have I…
-Because I don't think

828
00:35:46,240 --> 00:35:49,535
you've been on Earth long
enough even at a rate of two per day.

829
00:35:49,619 --> 00:35:52,371
-Okay, what is happening?
-What do you mean, "What is happening"?

830
00:35:52,455 --> 00:35:54,039
-Have you not been paying attention?
-She never pays attention.

831
00:35:54,123 --> 00:35:55,374
Our whole lives are
going down the toilet.

832
00:35:55,458 --> 00:35:57,710
-Where the hell have you been?
-She's been out.

833
00:35:57,794 --> 00:35:59,211
Doing whatever it is she does at night.

834
00:35:59,295 --> 00:36:00,963
Oh, and I suppose that's my fault, too.

835
00:36:01,047 --> 00:36:02,965
-You know what I'm doing at night.
-If you hadn't met me,

836
00:36:03,049 --> 00:36:04,174
then I wouldn't be Miriam's mother

837
00:36:04,258 --> 00:36:05,843
and she wouldn't be
turning to prostitution

838
00:36:05,927 --> 00:36:08,053
-instead of being married.
-I am not a prostitute. I'm a comic.

839
00:36:08,137 --> 00:36:10,806
-Is there a difference?
-Yes, prostitutes get paid more.

840
00:36:10,890 --> 00:36:12,016
Hilarious.

841
00:36:12,100 --> 00:36:14,351
-You should go into comedy.
-I did.

842
00:36:14,435 --> 00:36:16,770
I can't deal with you now.
I have enough to worry about.

843
00:36:16,854 --> 00:36:18,230
Yes. You have to figure
out where we're gonna live.

844
00:36:18,314 --> 00:36:19,314
-Okay.
-How we're gonna pay for it.

845
00:36:19,398 --> 00:36:20,941
-Enough.
-And the going rate of Zelda.

846
00:36:21,025 --> 00:36:23,067
-So you took it out on my clothes?
-He saved you the trouble.

847
00:36:23,151 --> 00:36:25,069
You have to move them
anyway because this is not

848
00:36:25,153 --> 00:36:25,963
our home anymore.

849
00:36:26,047 --> 00:36:28,281
It was never ours.
Columbia always owned it.

850
00:36:28,365 --> 00:36:29,866
We would've had to move eventually.

851
00:36:29,950 --> 00:36:32,285
-Yes, when we died.
-Still, a deadline.

852
00:36:32,369 --> 00:36:33,703
-Oh.
-Blue dress, blue dress.

853
00:36:33,787 --> 00:36:36,414
-What are you doing?
-I need a dress for tonight.

854
00:36:36,498 --> 00:36:38,958
You see? Selfish.
That's the daughter that we raised.

855
00:36:39,042 --> 00:36:40,752
Now wait a minute, don't turn

856
00:36:40,836 --> 00:36:42,462
whatever this fight is around on me.

857
00:36:42,546 --> 00:36:44,213
I am hardly the selfish one here.

858
00:36:44,297 --> 00:36:45,882
What does that mean?

859
00:36:45,966 --> 00:36:47,759
I couldn't believe it when
Mama told me what you did.

860
00:36:47,843 --> 00:36:50,011
-What I did when?
-Columbia? Quitting?

861
00:36:50,095 --> 00:36:52,430
Giving up the apartment?
I am still in shock.

862
00:36:52,514 --> 00:36:54,432
That situation has
nothing to do with you.

863
00:36:54,516 --> 00:36:56,350
What are you talking about? I live here.

864
00:36:56,434 --> 00:36:57,810
My children live here.

865
00:36:57,894 --> 00:36:59,437
But you shouldn't be
living here, should you?

866
00:36:59,521 --> 00:37:00,646
You shouldn't be living here,

867
00:37:00,730 --> 00:37:01,898
your children shouldn't be living here.

868
00:37:01,982 --> 00:37:03,357
You should be living with your husband,

869
00:37:03,441 --> 00:37:06,360
-at your own place.
-My husband walked out.

870
00:37:06,444 --> 00:37:08,112
Sure, but then another one walked in.

871
00:37:08,196 --> 00:37:09,363
Yes, a doctor.

872
00:37:09,447 --> 00:37:11,365
What the hell happened
with Benjamin anyway?

873
00:37:11,449 --> 00:37:13,326
-You know what happened with Benjamin.
-ABE: No.

874
00:37:13,410 --> 00:37:13,639
